    <div class="phase-hdr" style="border-bottom-color:var(--green2);"><div class="ph-num" style="background:var(--green2);color:#fff;">2</div><div><div class="ph-title">IDENTIFY &amp; DECONFLICT <span style="color:#A0C8B0;font-size:9px;font-style:italic;font-family:var(--bf);font-weight:400;"> â€” Authority First</span></div><div class="ph-sub" style="color:#7EC89A;">Confirm authorization status Â· Determine jurisdiction before any action</div></div></div>
    <div class="pb-body pb2">
      <div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">âœ…</span><div><span class="bi-lbl cg">Confirm Authorization â€”</span><span class="bi-txt"> Valid COA? LAANC clearance? Federal mission authorization? Check NOTAM active status with FAA.</span></div></div>
      <div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">âš–ï¸</span><div><span class="bi-lbl cg">Determine Jurisdiction â€”</span><span class="bi-txt"> Is the UAS over Â§130i-covered (DoD) or Â§124n-covered (DHS) space â€” or is it transiting between both?</span></div></div>
      <div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">ğŸ“</span><div><span class="bi-lbl cg">Mandatory Notifications â€”</span><span class="bi-txt"> Notify: <strong>FAA ATCSCC</strong> (airspace) Â· <strong>FBI/DOJ</strong> (criminal nexus) Â· <strong>State/Local LE</strong> (public safety).</span></div></div>
      <div class="al a-warn" style="margin-top:4px;"><span class="al-ico">âš </span><span><strong>Â§130i â†” Â§124n Handoff:</strong> When threat transits between DoD and DHS jurisdictional space, the pre-designated Interagency Coordination Cell (ICC) manages authority transfer in real time. Do not act without confirmed authority.</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="conn">â–¼</div>

  <div class="phase-blk">
    <div class="phase-hdr" style="border-bottom-color:var(--red2);"><div class="ph-num" style="background:var(--red2);color:#fff;">3</div><div><div class="ph-title">MITIGATE <span style="color:#D09090;font-size:9px;font-style:italic;font-family:var(--bf);font-weight:400;"> â€” Controlled &amp; Proportional</span></div><div class="ph-sub" style="color:#E09090;">Apply directional measures Â· Avoid broad-spectrum in dense infrastructure zones</div></div></div>
    <div class="pb-body pb3">
      <div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">ğŸ“¶</span><div><span class="bi-lbl cr">Directed RF Disruption â€”</span><span class="bi-txt"> Narrowband jamming where authorized. Avoid broad-spectrum near hospitals, emergency comms, and telecom infrastructure.</span></div></div>
      <div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">ğŸ›°</span><div><span class="bi-lbl cr">GNSS Denial / Spoofing â€”</span><span class="bi-txt"> Only where authorized by SecDef/SecDHS delegation AND FAA coordination is complete. Document all actions.</span></div></div>
      <div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">ğŸ¯</span><div><span class="bi-lbl cr">Physical / Kinetic â€”</span><span class="bi-txt"> Last resort. Requires command authority, clear airspace, ROE compliance. Urban backdrop must be confirmed clear.</span></div></div>
      <div class="al a-danger" style="margin-top:4px;"><span class="al-ico">ğŸš¨</span><span><strong>Assess risk before ANY mitigation:</strong> Emergency services Â· Hospitals Â· Telecom infrastructure Â· GPS-dependent transport Â· Civilian presence Â· Media visibility Â· Legal constraints.</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="kfbar"><span class="kf-lbl">ğŸ“‹ Key Factor:</span><span> Mitigation authority is NOT automatic. Verify Â§130i or Â§124n delegation is in effect, FAA coordination is complete, and ROE compliance confirmed before any active countermeasure.</span></div>
</div>

