  <div class="sb">
    <div class="sbh sbhh-red"><span class="sbh-ico">ğŸ¤</span><span class="sbh-txt">Interagency Coordination Matrix</span><span class="sbh-sub">â€” Pre-establish relationships before incident</span></div>
    <div class="sbb sb-red" style="padding:4px 5px;">
      <div class="coord-row"><div class="coord-ag ca-faa">FAA<br>ATCSCC</div><div class="coord-bd"><strong>Mandatory notification</strong> before active mitigation. Coordinate COA, NOTAM, and TFR. Immediate alert if GNSS interference detected. Primary airspace authority â€” no mitigation without FAA coordination.</div></div>
      <div class="coord-row"><div class="coord-ag ca-fbi">FBI /<br>DOJ</div><div class="coord-bd"><strong>Criminal nexus determination.</strong> FBI assumes Lead Federal Agency (LFA) role if hostile actor involved. Coordinate evidence preservation. Do not destroy UAS if criminal investigation likely.</div></div>
      <div class="coord-row"><div class="coord-ag ca-sta">State /<br>Local LE</div><div class="coord-bd"><strong>Pre-established MOU/MOA required.</strong> Perimeter security, public safety corridors, civilian evacuation. Jurisdiction boundary awareness critical at urban environments and high-traffic areas.</div></div>
      <div class="coord-row"><div class="coord-ag ca-icc">ICC<br>Â§130iâ†”<br>Â§124n</div><div class="coord-bd"><strong>Interagency Coordination Cell:</strong> Manages real-time authority handoff when UAS transits DoD â†” DHS jurisdictional space. Must be pre-designated and staffed before any incident.</div></div>
      <div class="coord-row" style="border-bottom:none;"><div class="coord-ag ca-jag">JAG /<br>Counsel</div><div class="coord-bd"><strong>All mitigation actions reviewed</strong> within 24 hrs by JAG (DoD) or Chief Counsel (DHS). Real-time legal consult available to site commander. Congressional notification chain required.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sb">
    <div class="sbh sbhh-navy"><span class="sbh-ico">ğŸ“‹</span><span class="sbh-txt">Post-Incident Reporting Requirements</span></div>
    <div class="sbb sb-gray">
      <div class="rep-item"><div class="rep-lbl" style="color:#8B1A1A;">â± INTREP â€” Within 1 Hour</div>Submit Incident Report: time, location, UAS description, threat assessment, action taken, collateral effects, and authority exercised (Â§130i or Â§124n).</div>
      <div class="rep-item"><div class="rep-lbl" style="color:#1A3A6A;">âœˆ FAA Notification â€” Immediate</div>Notify FAA upon any RF mitigation affecting the NAS. Include: frequencies affected, duration, geographic area, and mitigation type.</div>
      <div class="rep-item"><div class="rep-lbl" style="color:#1A5C2A;">âš– Legal Review â€” Within 24 Hours</div>JAG (DoD) or Chief Counsel (DHS) reviews all mitigation actions. Document proportionality determination and authority basis for each action taken.</div>
      <div class="rep-item"><div class="rep-lbl" style="color:#5A4000;">ğŸ› Congressional Notification</div>SecDef / SecDHS statutory obligation to report Â§130i / Â§124n actions to Congress. Unit commanders feed accuracy into upward reporting chain promptly.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sb">
    <div class="sbh sbhh-orange"><span class="sbh-ico">ğŸ›¡</span><span class="sbh-txt">Survivability &amp; Urban Protection Principles</span></div>
    <div class="sbb sb-gray">
      <div class="urban-grid">
        <div class="uc"><span class="uc-icon">ğŸ“¡</span><span class="uc-title">Electronic Signature</span><br>C-UAS systems emit detectable RF. Reposition after active emissions. Signal reflections amplify detectability in urban canyons.</div>
        <div class="uc"><span class="uc-icon">ğŸ—</span><span class="uc-title">Structural Cover</span><br>Operate from hardened positions. Assume adversary UAS carries EO/IR payload and can surveil your position.</div>
        <div class="uc"><span class="uc-icon">ğŸ”€</span><span class="uc-title">Act, Reposition, Reassess</span><br>Urban terrain is dynamic. Change position after each electronic emission. Avoid pattern predictability.</div>
        <div class="uc"><span class="uc-icon">ğŸ‘</span><span class="uc-title">Layered Overwatch</span><br>No single sensor covers all azimuths &amp; elevations. Maintain overlapping multi-sensor coverage across team.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sb" style="margin-bottom:5px;">
    <div class="sbh sbhh-navy"><span class="sbh-ico">ğŸŒ†</span><span class="sbh-txt">Urban Notes: Populated Environment Factors</span></div>
    <div class="sbb sb-blue">
      <div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">ğŸ‘¥</span><div><span class="bi-lbl cn">Civilian Presence â€”</span><span class="bi-txt"> Non-combatant proximity limits all mitigation options. Broad-spectrum jamming prohibited near hospitals, emergency services, and telecom nodes.</span></div></div>
      <div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">ğŸ“°</span><div><span class="bi-lbl cn">Media Visibility â€”</span><span class="bi-txt"> Assume C-UAS operations in urban environments and high-traffic areas are visible to media. All actions must be legally defensible and proportional.</span></div></div>
      <div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">ğŸ›«</span><div><span class="bi-lbl cn">Class B/C Airspace â€”</span><span class="bi-txt"> FAA NOTAM coordination and COA required before any active EW mitigation affecting NAS.</span></div></div>
      <div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">ğŸ—º</span><div><span class="bi-lbl cn">Jurisdictional Boundaries â€”</span><span class="bi-txt"> Military installation perimeters may not align with municipal, county, or state authority lines. Map boundaries pre-incident.</span></div></div>
    </div>
