<div class="sec-lbl sl-follow"><div class="sl-num" style="background:var(--green2);color:#fff;">III</div>PHASE 3 â€” FOLLOW-ON ACTIONS: Post-Engagement Â· Reporting Â· Reset Â· Lessons Learned</div>

<div class="cols4">
  <!-- Immediate -->
  <div class="col">
    <div class="chdr chh-red"><span class="chdr-icon">â±</span><div><div class="chdr-title">Immediate (0â€“15 min)</div><div class="chdr-sub">On-site actions after engagement ends</div></div></div>
    <div style="padding:5px 6px;">
      <div class="tl-step"><div class="tl-num" style="background:var(--red2);color:#fff;">1</div><div><div class="tl-title" style="color:var(--red2);">Cease Fire / Secure</div><div class="tl-body">Confirm threat neutralized. Cease all active EW and kinetic. Restore normal FAA airspace status. Alert all sensors to resume monitoring posture.</div></div></div>
      <div class="tl-step"><div class="tl-num" style="background:var(--red2);color:#fff;">2</div><div><div class="tl-title" style="color:var(--red2);">Site Security / Cordon</div><div class="tl-body">If UAS downed: establish 25-meter cordon. Treat as potential IED. Do NOT approach until EOD clearance. Notify FBI if criminal nexus.</div></div></div>
      <div class="tl-step"><div class="tl-num" style="background:var(--red2);color:#fff;">3</div><div><div class="tl-title" style="color:var(--red2);">Casualties / Collateral</div><div class="tl-body">Assess friendly casualties and any civilian collateral effects. Initiate medical response. Document injuries and property damage for legal review.</div></div></div>
      <div class="tl-step"><div class="tl-num" style="background:var(--red2);color:#fff;">4</div><div><div class="tl-title" style="color:var(--red2);">Higher HQ Notification</div><div class="tl-body">Notify higher HQ immediately. Pass: SALUTE report on UAS, action taken, authority exercised (Â§130i / Â§124n), current site status, collateral assessment.</div></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <!-- Reporting -->
  <div class="col">
    <div class="chdr chh-orange"><span class="chdr-icon">ğŸ“‹</span><div><div class="chdr-title">Reporting (15 min â€“ 24 hr)</div><div class="chdr-sub">Statutory and operational reporting requirements</div></div></div>
    <div style="padding:5px 6px;">
      <div class="sb"><div class="sbh sbhh-red"><span class="sbh-ico">âš¡</span><span class="sbh-txt">Within 1 Hour â€” INTREP</span></div><div class="sbb sb-red"><div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">ğŸ“</span><span class="bi-txt">Submit Incident Report: time/date, site location, UAS group/type, approach vector, threat indicators, action taken, authority exercised (Â§130i or Â§124n), collateral effects, current status.</span></div></div></div>
      <div class="sb"><div class="sbh sbhh-navy"><span class="sbh-ico">âœˆ</span><span class="sbh-txt">Immediate â€” FAA Notification</span></div><div class="sbb sb-blue"><div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">ğŸ“</span><span class="bi-txt">Notify FAA ATCSCC: frequencies affected, duration of EW, geographic footprint, type of mitigation, and whether NAS was impacted. Coordinate NOTAM closure if TFR was activated.</span></div></div></div>
      <div class="sb"><div class="sbh sbhh-steel"><span class="sbh-ico">ğŸ”µ</span><span class="sbh-txt">Within 4 Hours â€” Applicable Law Enforcement</span></div><div class="sbb sb-gray"><div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">ğŸ“</span><span class="bi-txt">If UAS recovered: notify applicable law enforcement (FBI, state, or local LE depending on jurisdiction) for criminal investigation determination. Preserve chain of custody â€” do not handle UAS without gloves. Do not power down if found active.</span></div></div></div>
      <div class="sb"><div class="sbh sbhh-orange"><span class="sbh-ico">âš–</span><span class="sbh-txt">Within 24 Hours â€” Legal Review</span></div><div class="sbb sb-orange"><div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">âš–</span><span class="bi-txt">JAG (DoD) or Chief Counsel (DHS) reviews all mitigation actions. Proportionality assessment. Document authority basis for each action. Flag any ROE deviations for immediate review.</span></div></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <!-- Exploitation -->
  <div class="col">
    <div class="chdr chh-steel"><span class="chdr-icon">ğŸ”</span><div><div class="chdr-title">Exploitation &amp; Intelligence</div><div class="chdr-sub">Turn the engagement into advantage</div></div></div>
    <div style="padding:5px 6px;">
      <div class="sb">
        <div class="sbh sbhh-steel"><span class="sbh-ico">ğŸ”</span><span class="sbh-txt">UAS Exploitation (if recovered)</span></div>
        <div class="sbb sb-blue">
          <div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">ğŸ“·</span><div><span class="bi-lbl cs">Document in place: </span><span class="bi-txt">Photograph UAS before any handling. Note final position, orientation, and any payload indicators visible.</span></div></div>
          <div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">ğŸ”¬</span><div><span class="bi-lbl cs">EOD Clearance: </span><span class="bi-txt">No handling until EOD confirms safe. Group 2 payload risk requires bomb squad before any exploitation begins.</span></div></div>
          <div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">ğŸ’»</span><div><span class="bi-lbl cs">Digital Forensics: </span><span class="bi-txt">Preserve flight logs, SD cards, and control hardware. Pass to FBI/NCIS for exploitation. Do not factory-reset or power cycle.</span></div></div>
          <div class="bi"><span class="bi-ico">ğŸ·</span><div><span class="bi-lbl cs">Serial Numbers: </span><span class="bi-txt">Document all serial numbers (airframe, battery, controller). FAA UAS registry lookup may identify registered owner.</span></div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="sb">
        <div class="sbh sbhh-navy"><span class="sbh-ico">ğŸ“¡</span><span class="sbh-txt">RF / Signal Intelligence</span></div>
